        public boolean haveCached(Address origin,
                 Address destination)
        Checks if a DrivingDirections object for a given source and destination address is in the cache. No new driving directions will be requested if they are not found in the cache.
        Parameters:
        origin - an Address to get directions from. Should already be Geocoded.
        destination - an Address to get directions to. Should already be Geocoded.
        Returns:
        true if there are cached directions for this pair of Geocodables.

      • getCached

        destination - an Address to get directions to. Should already be Geocoded.

      • getDirections

        public DrivingDirections getDirections(Address origin,
                              Address destination,
                              com.guidewire.commons.entity.BundleProvider bundleProvider)
        Returns a DrivingDirections object for a given source and destination address. Driving directions will be requested from the Geocoding service if they are not found in the cache. This can be slow.

        Any newly requested directions will have directions and maps in the System Default Unit of Distance.

        Parameters:
        origin - an Address to get directions from. Should already be Geocoded.
        destination - an Address to get directions to. Should already be Geocoded.
        Returns:
        a DrivingDirections object, or null if no directions were found.

      • getDirections

        public DrivingDirections getDirections(Address origin,
                              Address destination,
                              boolean cachedOnly,
                              com.guidewire.commons.entity.BundleProvider bundleProvider)
        Returns a DrivingDirections object for a given source and destination address. Note that the cachedOnly parameter has a large effect on the behavior of this method:
        - if cachedOnly is set to true, no new driving directions will be requested if they are not found in the cache.
        - if cachedOnly is set to false. driving directions will be requested from the Geocoding service if they are not found in the cache. This can be slow.

        Any newly requested directions will have directions and maps in the System Default Unit of Distance.

        Parameters:
        origin - an Address to get directions from. Should already be Geocoded.
        destination - an Address to get directions to. Should already be Geocoded.
        cachedOnly - if true, check for cached driving directions, but do not generate new driving directions if not cached
        Returns:
        a DrivingDirections object, or null if no directions were found.

      • getDirections

        public DrivingDirections getDirections(Address origin,
                              Address destination,
                              boolean cachedOnly,
                              UnitOfDistance unit,
                              com.guidewire.commons.entity.BundleProvider bundleProvider)
        Returns a DrivingDirections object for a given source and destination address. Note that the cachedOnly parameter has a large effect on the behavior of this method:
        - if cachedOnly is set to true, no new driving directions will be requested if they are not found in the cache.
        - if cachedOnly is set to false. driving directions will be requested from the Geocoding service if they are not found in the cache. This can be slow.
        Parameters:
        origin - an Address to get directions from. Should already be Geocoded.
        destination - an Address to get directions to. Should already be Geocoded.
        cachedOnly - if true, check for cached driving directions, but do not generate new driving directions if not cached
        unit - a unitOfdistance TypeKey, indicating whether to use miles or kilometers in newly requested directions (cached directions will not be affected.)
        Returns:
        a DrivingDirections object, or null if no directions were found.

      • getSelectedDirections

        public void getSelectedDirections(CommonContact[] contacts,
                         com.guidewire.pl.system.service.search.CommonContactSearchCriteria csc)
        Gets the driving directions for those selected (checked) users on a Contact (Address Book) search LV. Normally this is invoked in the allCheckedRowsAction of a CheckedValuesToolbarButton widget. Note that there are three very similar functions, for Contacts, Users, GroupUser/User Assignment searches.

        This will use the system-default unit of distance.

        Parameters:
        csc - the current ContactSearchCriteria for this SearchPanel (providing the origin for the directions through its proximitySearchCenter)
        contacts - the contacts to get directions to; normally the CheckedValues array
